The paper deals with the problem of defending against adversarial attacks on deep neural networks, which is a topic that falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also proposes a novel approach that involves using an ensemble of networks and a repeated Bayesian Stackelberg Game, which are techniques commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI). The experiments conducted in the paper involve image classification tasks, which are typically studied in computer vision (cs.CV). Lastly, the paper also mentions the concept of multi-agent systems, which is a topic that falls under the category of control and optimization (cs.SY).
